28-year-old cook found dead in the shopping mall of San Francisco
A 28-year-old cook, who recently moved to San Francisco, was found dead in the stairwell flight of the local shopping center this week.
But the brother of the victim says that he cannot imagine someone who would like to hurt him, noting: "Finly things he went to his way."
- The body found in Westfield Mall on Wednesday morning was identified as a 28-year-old resident of San Francisco Frank Galicia, - reported San Francisco's Forensic Expertise Bureau.
The San Francisco Police Department reports that death was classified as murder and investigation continues.
The victim's brother, Luiz Galicia, told KGO TV and Radio Company ABC in San Francisco that Frank, the past chef of the hand line in Boston, got his dream job as a cook at the San Francisco's Sons &amp; Daughters restaurant six months ago.
The Sons &amp; Daughters representative said they were "shocked and suppressed" by his death.
"We are a small team that works as a friendly family and it will be very short of it," the representative said.
Our thoughts and condolences to Frank's family and friends during this difficult period.
Luiz Galicia said that Frank first stayed at hostels, but recently "Finally he was doing business."
"He found an apartment, he met a girl," Luis Galicia said to KGO.
Luis Galicia said that he could not imagine someone who would like to hurt his younger brother.
He had a good soul and a great heart.
His way of contacting the family was always to prepare us some dish, cook us dinner," said Luis Galicia.
He never wanted to be involved in any quarrel.
He was a brother who was sailing with the current.
"With all the bad things that happen to this world, he was the unlimited diamond that brightly shone every day," he said.
All who own information are asked to call the SFPD Hot Line at 415-575-4444.
