Italy's public debt increased to record levels
The size of the Italian public debt in June 2016 exceeded 2.248 trillion euros.
The central bank of the country said that this amount is a historical maximum, RIA Novosti reports.
The previous negative record was set in May this year.
Then the government debt reached 2.228 trillion euros.
It is noted that in the first half of the year Italy's debt burden increased by 77.2 billion euros.
Earlier it was reported that at the end of 2015 the state debt of Italy was 132.7% of the country's GDP.
Meanwhile, Italian Minister of Economy and Finance Pier Carlo Padoan predicted a decline in this indicator in 2016 to 130.9%, and in 2018 - to 123.4% of GDP.
Payments from the airport received 141 victims of the terrorist attack in Domodedovo.
141 people received charitable payments from the "Aviation" Foundation, which was created by the management of the airport "Domodedovo" to help the victims of the terrorist attack in 2011, Interfax reports.
According to the press secretary of the airport Alexander Vlasov, now there are two more statements on consideration.
"The fund continues to pay charitable payments to victims of the 2011 terrorist attack and provides comprehensive assistance to address existing issues," Vlasov added, reminding that specifically to facilitate interaction with the victims, the Foundation's website was created, containing full information on the procedure for providing charitable assistance.
In 2011, in the arrival hall of foreign airlines Domodedovo, the suicide bomber put an explosive device into operation.
As a result of the attack 37 people were killed, another 172 were injured.
Scientists have found an animal that can live 500 years
The international group of biologists concluded that the longest-lived vertebrates are the Greenland polar shark, which can live for about 500 years, reports RT.
Scientists conducted a radiocarbon analysis of the eye lens of 28 Greenland sharks.
The largest kurk, whose length exceeds five meters, can be from 272 to 512 years.
Biologists believe that a low metabolism plays an important role in the longevity of sharks, which leads to slow development.
Females of Greenland sharks reach puberty only by 150 years.
Earlier it was believed that the longest vertebrates live "neighbor" sharks - the Greenland hood.
The oldest individual, known to the scientist, was a little older than 210 years.
