What does Russia point to the crisis?
Economists saw signs of Russia's withdrawal from the longest recession in the last twenty years.
According to analysts surveyed by Bloomberg, GDP of the Russian Federation shows positive dynamics - in the second quarter GDP decreased by 0.8% in annual terms.
This indicator is minimal since the beginning of 2015.
According to the latest Rosstat data, the decline in the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed down to 0.6%.
The Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development also announced the stabilization of the situation recently.
Ahead - a slow growth.
According to experts of the CBR, the recession in the Russian economy has remained in the past.
"The index estimate of the Russian GDP indicates that the recession remained behind, and ahead - a slow growth of the economy," the Bank of Russia says in the bulletin "What Trends Say."
The regulator's modular GDP estimate for the current quarter increased to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter is 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development, during the second quarter GDP decline stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter seasonally refined GDP decline amounted to 0.2% QoQ.
But during the quarter the decline stopped: in April it was 0.2%, and in May and June the GDP change was within 0-0.15," the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development of RIA Novosti quotes.
The slowdown in the Russian economy's decline over the past five quarters shows that "the day has been over."
Among other tokens pointing to signs of revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls the growth of demand for electricity and rail transportation, the revival of the business.
If you make an amendment to the fact that the leap year, it is clear that the dynamics of plus 1% of electricity consumption can be half due to an additional working day.
Add to this a lower average annual temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight transportation, but it is difficult to obtain accurate data, and plus-minus 0.5% of the half-year volume can also be explained by seasonality," explains Kirill Yakovenko from ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of stabilization of the Russian economy.
For example, lowering price pressure.
In July, consumer price index was 7.2% compared to 15.6% in the same month last year.
Moreover, the last two weeks Rosstat records deflection.
Prices in Russia declined for the first time in five years.
If you look at the dynamics of the ruble, which, although showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, after August, has strengthened by 12% since the beginning of the year.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy," Yakovenko emphasizes.
In addition, since April in Russia there is an increase in industrial production.
In June, the figure rose by 1.7%.
The rate of decline in foreign trade turnover from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May slow down.
Positive dynamics also demonstrate the situation in the labor market, where the unemployment rate decreased to 5.4%.
Below it was only in September 2015 (5.2%).
Despite the safe situation in the labor market, the issue with real available incomes of the population to leave much to be desired.
In annual terms, the figure is reduced by 4.8%.
This factor can inhibit the recovery of the economy, as household expenditures make a considerable contribution to the GDP.
As a rule, in the structure of the economy their share exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, the Bank of Russia's tough policy can also be called as risk factors for economic growth.
The regulator holds the rate at 10.5%, which is not the best effect on the real sector.
Negative factor is not high level of investment, which restrains the development of industrial potential.
But in general, we can assume that by the end of the year the rate of the Russian economy will slow down to -0.5% against -3.7% in 2015," - says Irina Rogov, analyst of the State Committee of Forex Club.
The process of naturalization of athletes, recently launched in Russian football and perfectly in the winter sports at the Olympic Games in Sochi, is not so actively developed in summer sports.
If in the Olympic Games in Rio for Russia and speak former foreigners, in most cases we are talking about the natives of the countries - the former republics of the Soviet Union.
But in Rio de Janeiro, we can observe the reverse process - quite a large number of Russians perform under the flags of other countries.
In each case, the history of changing citizenship is different.
Some parents were taken to another country as a child, leaving no choice.
Someone did not stand the competition for a place in the Russian team.
And someone considered that abroad will be created the best conditions for development in sports.
"AiF.ru" found at least 16 athletes who decided to change their Russian citizenship.
In the German passport of 27-year-old girl it is written that her name is Lisa Ryzhikh.
But earlier she was, of course, Elizabeth.
She was born in 1988 in the city of Omsk.
Just four years later, as soon as the Soviet Union collapsed, Lisa's parents decided to emigrate to Germany.
The girl had no choice.
There she decided to go in the footsteps of her elder sister - to engage in athletics.
Just like her sister, Lisa chose pole jumps.
She stayed in Russia, it would hardly be able to "move from the throne" Elena Isinbayeva.
Unfortunately, at the Olympics in Rio Lisa will be the only countryman, albeit former, in the sector for pole jumps.
Its best achievements in this sport - the bronze of the European Championship 2010 and silver continental championship in 2016, which she won again in the absence of Elena Isinbayeva.
29-year-old Elena Pirozhkova was born in Novokuznetsk in 1986.
Her parents are religious propagandists of the evangelistic direction.
Many of them because of their faith, they left for the United States when the girl was only three years old.
In addition to Elena, eight more children grew up in the family.
They all lived in a small town of Greenfield in Massachusetts.
Lena began to get carried away by the struggle at school.
Showing good results, she moved to Colorado Springs, where at the US Training Center continued classes under the guidance of another former Russian Vladislav Izboynikov.
At the 2012 Olympics in London, Elena lost in her first battle.
But at the World Cup in the same year - a victory.
Before that, by the way, she managed to win silver at the world championship in 2010.
After that there were bronze 2013 and silver 2014.
26-year-old Maria was born in Yaroslavl, where she first met with synchronized swimming.
But it would be wrong to say that it was brought up by our coaches in Russia.
Soon the girl's family decided to emigrate to the United States and settle in Colorado.
There Freya continued her classes.
Soon she was already a member of the U.S. national team and showed great results at the Pan-American Games.
It is clear that at a serious international level, it cannot compete with Russian synchronists, but for America its indicators are the ceiling.
The new name, which sounds strange in Russian, Kristina Shaldybin received at the age of 11, when her parents decided to continue training the girl rhythmic gymnastics over the ocean.
Until then, the girl was engaged in her favorite sport in her native Yaroslavl.
Having emigrated to the United States, she quickly joined the youth team of this country, and later burst into the main national team.
At the Pan-American Games 19-year-old Christen won gold and silver.
For the first position on the world stage, of course, it did not have to fight, but for the United States she organized a real breakthrough - brought a star-striped team to the Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro.
Another of our former "artress" - Jana Berezko-Marggrander, who stands for the national team of Germany.
Yana was born in Togliatti.
In 2008, when the girl was 13 years old, the family decided to move to Germany - there the girl had more prospects to get into the national team.
Soon she represented her country at the 2012 Olympic Games in London.
There, however, Jana was able to take only 17th place, insufficient to get into the finals in the individual championship.
But two years before that, she managed to win the bronze medal of the Olympic Games - youth.
Another gymnast, only this time sports - Irina Sazonova.
If the ways of emigration of the previously mentioned athletes can be called standard, then the choice of Irina's family is very unusual - Iceland.
Ira is a pupil of Volgograd sports school.
Naturally, in Iceland, she immediately became the champion of the country.
However, Ira is still training in Russia - he specially comes to his homeland in order not to lose his skills.
In Rio she did not perform as well as she would like.
The best place - 40 in the individual all-around.
There are very few reports about swimmer Maria Ugolkova in the Russian information space.
For a very long time, Maria lives and trains in Switzerland.
However, for a long time she performed under the Russian flag, showing good results - there was even a record of the country at a distance of 200 meters butterfly.
In 2015, she received Swiss citizenship and began to perform under the red and white flag.
In Rio, her best performance - 14th place in the complex relay 4x100.
To get on the game, the girl launched a crowdfunding project, thanks to which she was able to collect about 6 thousand francs, which allowed her to pay for the preparation for the Olympics.
31-year-old freestyle fighter Adam Batirov spent almost all his career under the Russian flag.
During this time, the native of Khasavyurt managed to become a three-time winner of the European Championships, the champion of Russia, the master of sports of Russia of international class.
When he stopped entering our national team, it's time to think about changing citizenship.
For several years, the talented fighter disappeared from the sports bridges.
The triumphal return took place at the Asian Championship 2016 - Batirov has already represented Bahrain, for whom he won the gold medal and received a ticket to the Olympic Games in Rio.
About another ex-Russian, Mikhail Kudinov, is even less known in his homeland than even about the Swiss swimmer Maria Ugolkov.
The fact is that his parents emigrated from Vladivostok to New Zealand, when the boy was quite small.
It was there that Mikhail began to engage in gymnastics.
He did not achieve great success at the international level.
In Rio, his best result was 40th place in qualification on parallel bars.
But for New Zealand, even getting to the Olympic Games in gymnastics - already a breakthrough.
When Nast, who was born in Moscow in 1985, was only 9 years old, her family emigrated to Israel.
There the girl continued her classes synchronous swimming, showing good results at the national level.
In 2014, at the European Championships in Berlin, the girl took 6th place in synchronized swimming.
In a duet with Eugenia Tetelbaum Anastasia took eighth place.
In the solo program she was the fifth.
Like Anastasia, 23-year-old Dmitry Croyter stands for the national team of Israel.
When the boy was only 6 years old, his mother decided to repatriate to Israel.
In 2009, at the age of 17, Dmitry has already become the champion of the country.
In the same year, he won in the youth world championship.
A year later, Croyter wins the gold of the Youth Olympic Games in Singapore.
In addition to jumping in height, Dmitry is engaged in jumping in length and triple jump.
Albert, 31, is another native of Khasavyurt, who after long speeches for Russia decided to change his sports citizenship.
However, unlike Batirov, Albert chose Romania, which will represent in Rio.
In Russia, he also played for the School of Higher Sports Mastery of Krasnoyarsk, in 2011 even becoming the champion of the country.
28-year-old Oleg Antonov was born in Moscow in the family of the USSR volleyball team player Yaroslav Antonov.
Just a year before the birth of his son, Yaroslav was recognized as the best volleyball player of the planet.
Soon he decided to continue his career in Italy.
There the family remained for permanent residence.
In 2015, as part of the national team, he won the bronze medal of the European Championship, held on the territory of his new homeland.
Hadzhiev was born in Chechnya in 1994 and got together with his family in the midst of the war.
Ten years later, parents decided to emigrate.
The original goal was Norway, but it was not possible to get to this northern country - had to go to France, to Nice.
There Zelimkhan continued to learn freestyle wrestling.
Soon he won the world championship among juniors, and later qualified for participation in the Olympic Games.
In Rio, he will be the only representative of France in the wrestling tournament.
And again a freestyle struggle, and again a former Russian.
This time we will talk about a native of North Ossetia, who emigrated to Spain - Taimuraz Fryeva.
At the end of December 2012, he was granted Spanish citizenship, and currently he stands for the national team of the country.
Before that, however, the 30-year-old athlete managed to note high results in Russia.
He became the bronze medalist of the country's championships in 2007 and 2008.
Tied from the failure to enter the national team, Taimuraz decided to change sports citizenship.
The last on our list is the Chechen boxer, born in 1995 in the capital of Dagestan Makhachkala, - Artur Biyarslanov.
When the boy was ten years old, parents took the family through Azerbaijan to Canada.
There Arthur, on the advice of his eldest brother, began to box.
Since then, Arthur three times became the champion of Canada, and in 2012 became the world champion among young people.
In 2015 Biyarslanov won the gold of the Pan-American Games, the first for his new homeland since 1975.
Head of the Presidential Administration Anton Vaino.
On Friday, August 12, Vladimir Putin appointed Anton Vaino as head of the presidential administration.
Earlier, Sergei Ivanov held this position.
"The head of state appointed Anton Vaino as the head of the presidential administration of the Russian Federation, having dismissed him from his post," the decree signed by Putin and published on the Kremlin website reads.
Since May 2012, Vaino was Deputy Head of the Presidential Administration.
Anton Eduardovich Vaino was born on 17 February 1972 in Tallinn.
Father - Eduard Vaino, Chairman of the Business Council of Cuba-Russia at the Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Russian Federation and Vice President for External Relations and Cooperation with Shareholders of AvtoVAZ OJSC.
Grandfather - Karl Vaino - from 1988 to 1988, the first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Estonia.
In 1996 he graduated from the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia, the Faculty of International Relations.
From 1996 to 2001 he worked at the Russian Embassy in Japan, then in the Second Department of Asia of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia.
From 2002 to 2004 he held various positions in the Office of the Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2004 to 2007 - Deputy Head of the Protocol-Organizational Department of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2007 to 2007 - First Deputy Head of the Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From October 2007 to April 2008 - Deputy Head of the Office of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On April 25, 2008, he was appointed head of the protocol of the Prime Minister of the Russian Federation, Deputy Head of the Government's Apparatus of the Russian Federation.
Since December 27, 2011 - Minister of the Russian Federation - Head of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On May 22, 2012 he was appointed deputy head of the Presidential Administration.
Freely speaks English and Japanese.
Acting State Counselor of the Russian Federation of the 1st Class (class rank is given by the Decree of the President of the Russian Federation dated January 22, 2008)
Diploma of the President of the Russian Federation (February 16, 2012) for merits in ensuring the activities of the Government of the Russian Federation and many years of conscientious work.
Gratitude of the President of the Russian Federation (November 24, 2005) for his merits in the preparation and holding of solemn events dedicated to the 60th anniversary of the Victory in the Great Patriotic War.
