For more than a year, the Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Points (HACCP) system has been in the Russian version of HACCP - risk analysis and critical control points - is mandatory for the use by producers and carriers of food, as well as catering companies in Russia, as a member of the Customs Union (CU).
Rospotrebnadzor's business inspections for compliance with these norms in St. Petersburg began in February 2015.
