HACCP as a system that takes into account the risks of working with food and preventing them, invented in the United States in the 1960s.
Then it was about the safety of food for astronauts.
Now the system is used in all food enterprises not only in the United States, but also in Canada and in the European Union.
Since February 2015, HACCP operates on the territory of the Customs Union.
The development and implementation of the system of business was 4 years (the requirement of HASSP appeared in the technical regulation of the CU in 2011).
However, both entrepreneurs and officials admit that most companies have not even heard about this norm.
Unfortunately, we were convinced for a long time that the norm concerns only food productions, and not restaurateurs, - said the head of the Public Council Elena Tsereteli.
Now everyone is trying to make up for lost.
