Moscow Gazstroybank remained without a license from the Central Bank.
On Friday, August 12, 2016, the Central Bank of Russia withdrew the license for banking operations from the credit organization Joint Commercial Bank "GAZTROYBANK," registered in Moscow.
According to the regulator, JSC "GAZSTROYBANK" carried out a highly risky credit policy associated with the placement of cash in low-quality assets.
Adequate assessment of the risks taken at the request of the supervisory body and a reliable reflection of the value of the bank's assets led to the credit organization of grounds for the implementation of measures to prevent bankruptcy.
In addition, the credit organization was involved in conducting dubious transit operations.
The bank has appointed a temporary administration validity until the date of appointment in a competitive manager or liquidator.
The powers of the executive bodies of the credit organization in accordance with the federal laws have been suspended.
JSC "GAZSTROYBANK" - a member of the deposit insurance system.
Recall that the payment of insurance compensation to the bank's depositors, including individual entrepreneurs, in accordance with the Federal Law No. 177-FZ "On insurance of deposits of individuals in banks of the Russian Federation" is provided in the amount of 100% balance of funds, but not more than 1.4 million rubles in total per depositor.
Payments, according to the Deposit Insurance Agency, will begin no later than August 26, 2016.
According to the reporting, by the value of assets of JSC "GAZSTROYBANK" as of August 1, 2016 took 335th place in the banking system of the Russian Federation.
