Several people have already been detained on suspicion of the organization of explosions.
According to preliminary data of the local police, the scale and peculiarities of the explosions indicate that they were directed against the military leaders of the country.
Attacks occurred on popular tourist resorts, including the beach Patong in the area of Phuket and the city of Hua-Hin, Trang and Surat-Tani.
After the arrival of the military junta to power in the country in 2014, the economic growth fell from 7.2% (2012) to 2.8% (2015), but tourism remained one of the few industries that demonstrated development.
In 2016, the country has already been visited by 14 million people, which is 1.5 million more than in 2015.
The first suspects in the preparation and organization of attacks have already been detained, police colonel Crisan Patanacharoen said.
It is too early to talk about the goals, he added, but the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the country "sure that they are not connected with international extremist groups."
It's too early to draw conclusions," said Mr. Patanacharoen.
But we know for sure that these incidents are not directly related to any kind of terrorism, in fact, they are local sabotage, and we are trying to identify those behind them.
The explosions occurred on the birthday of Queen of Thailand Sikrit.
The Thai junta considers the defense of the monarchy as one of its main priorities, so the incident is likely to be directed against it.
According to the statement of the police general Sichaya Shsshoparonerat, the bombs were exploded remotely with a difference of half an hour.
They were hidden inside the trees on the busy streets filled with tourists dining in restaurants.
It is already known that one of the four dead was a Thai girl who traded street food.
The other victims are still unknown, but it is known that they are residents of four foreign countries.
According to the Royal Police of Thailand, among them are four citizens of Germany, three subjects of the Netherlands, two Italian citizens and a citizen of Austria.
There are no Russians among the victims of explosions, the press service of the Federal Tourism Agency reported.
Local experts also attribute the explosions to the August 7 referendum, at which 61.4% of the population supported the draft new constitution.
He was prepared by a commission to draft a constitution, appointed by a military junta.
The voted should have determined whether they support the system in which the upper house of parliament is fully appointed by the military and has a significant role in the election of the Prime Minister of the country.
The new system was adopted and tested for the first time at the 2017 parliamentary elections.
Recall, May 22, 2014 in Thailand there was a military coup led by the commander of the army of the country Prayut Chan-Ocha.
According to him, the army was motivated by the ongoing political crisis and the lack of progress in negotiations between the government and the opposition.
The military established the National Council of Peace and Order, introduced a curfew and censorship, dispersed protesters and the upper house of parliament.
