The largest M&A transaction - KIT Finance Pension Administrator launched the pension market.
As a result, on the basis of the "Gazfond of Pension Savings" the pension fund with the volume of savings of about 373 billion rubles will be created.
On the launch of the procedure for combining four pension funds - "KIT Finance," "Promagrofond," "Heritie" and "Gazfond Pension Savings" - yesterday said the owner of 100% of the funds of LLC "KIT Finance Pension Administrator."
"The reorganization is carried out in coordination with the Central Bank, while observing the requirements of non-ruterior conditions of existing contracts," the company said.
The association is carried out on the basis of the "Gasfond of Pension Savings."
According to General Director of this pension fund Oleg Byaloshitsky, the merger of funds allows to solve several problems: expanding the geography of presence, concentration of resources for development, reduction of costs, replicating the best practices of each of the funds and optimization of corporate governance.
According to him, the approximate deadline for the completion of the consolidation is the second quarter of 2017.
As a result of the merger of the pension fund "Gazfond Pension Savings" will become the largest player in the market of the FPS.
According to the data as of March 31, the volume of pension savings of the merged funds exceeded 373 billion rubles.
As follows from the reporting on the fund website, the beneficiaries of their owner - "KIT Finance Pension Administrator" - are currently Anatoly Gavrilenko (through the LLC controlled by the LLC owns 65%) and NPF "Gazfond" (35%).
However, the unification of the group itself has launched much later competitors.
Thus, the NPF controlled by O1 group "Fuel" absorbed the "Stalfond" at the beginning of this year.
Currently, this joint pension fund is joining Uralsib and Russian Standard funds.
Nikolai Sidorov, general director of the Future pension fund, notes: "Unification into a single structure, in addition to reducing costs, it is necessary to solve structural problems."
Active work on consolidation of funds from April is carried out in the pension group "Safmar" - NPF "European," "Education and Science" and "Region Fund" should join the pension fund "Safmar" until the end of this year.
In 2017, they will be joined by the pension fund "Trust."
"The mergers of funds will give the effect of increasing control over risks, operating processes and expenditures," - noted in the pension group "Safmar."
A pause in the merger of funds, which was withstood by the "KIT Finance Pension Administrator," can be caused by several reasons, according to experts.
Until recently, the pension funds could not buy more than 40% of the issue of infrastructural bonds, which were actively placed by the group.
After the amendments were made to the Central Bank's decision in March this year, there are no such restrictions on a number of issuers that meet the regulatory requirements.
If necessary, the entire issue can be bought by one major player," - says the director of the group of ratings of financial institutions of AKRA Yuri Nogin.
Several leaders of the NPF from the top 15 on assets are another possible cause of the pause and, as a consequence, personnel appointments in a single fund, which were to be harmonized by the group's owners.
Yesterday, Anatoly Gavrilenko was unavailable for comments.
The request of "K" in the NPF "Gazfond" also did not respond.
Although the consolidation of funds is a laborious and expensive event, this decision will be justified at a long distance.
