The Spiritual Administration of Muslims (Mum) of Tatarstan refuses to use the Russian language in mosques.
Yesterday, the plenary session of the DUM obliged its imams to conduct Friday sermons only in Tatar, to make young Tatars "to learn their native language."
The management states that this "in no way infringes" the rights of Muslims of other nationalities.
In some mosques Kazan complain that the Tatar language does not understand up to 60% of parishioners, including foreign students, migrants and Tatars themselves.
Imams fear that their sermons in the Tatar "will not reach the whole audience."
Yesterday, the plenary session of the Tatarstan DUM unanimously decided to hold Friday sermons in mosques of the republic only in the Tatar language.
According to Mufti of Tatarstan Kamil Samigullin, this should be an incentive for young Tatars to "learn their native language."
"For those who say that it is "heavy," in every big mosque we intend to organize lessons of the Tatar language for free," Mr. Samigullin promised.
He added that "the decision has already come into force" and today in all mosques the sermon "should be already in the Tatar language."
He recalled that the Duma of Tatarstan publishes the magazine "Shur" with typical sermons in the Tatar language.
Imam, who speaks Tatar well insufficiently, "may prepare for them thoroughly."
The Tatarstan DUM unites more than a thousand parishes in all municipalities of the republic.
According to Mufti, in the districts of Friday sermons are conducted exclusively in the Tatar language.
At the same time, in a number of mosques previously used predominantly Russian language.
In particular, as the mufti pointed out, this was practiced in the Burnaev mosque, Zakabannaya and Eniler.
However, Mukhametshin stressed that the leadership sets the task for all students to speak both state languages of the republic, regardless of nationality.
"There can be no question of any infringement of the Muslim-netatar," said Mr. Mukhametshin, explaining that the sermon itself "is not a mandatory, the main part of the namaz."
At the same time, the namaz itself will still be read in Arabic, in mosques there will be lectures and lessons in Russian.
At the same time, Rafik Mukhametshin said that there was no serious threat of expulsion of the Tatar language from mosques.
In addition to Russian and Tatar other languages, for example, Uzbek or Tajik, according to him, are not used in preaching in the republic.
The decision of the DUM was actively supported by the Executive Committee of the World Congress of Tatars (WCT).
Head of the Executive Committee of VKT Rinat Zakirov said: "Mecheti is an important part of our national life."
It would be sad if the Tatar language had left this sphere.
He noted that the conduct of sermons only in the Tatar language "desir of imams themselves," but in the executive committee of the VCT " consider this correct."
The imams, who preached in Russian, are ready to fulfill the decision of the DUM, but believe that the parishioners will have difficulties with understanding the clergy.
The mosque is both Tatars and Russians.
Many people do not understand the language.
They, of course, will be tight.
"We've had to rebuild," says Farhat Mavletdinov, Imam of the Burnaev Mosque.
According to him, the Russian language's sermons are closer to many Tatars, since "Russian and in schools, and in kindergartens, on the radio - everywhere initially."
However, he believes that the mosque will be able to continue lessons and lectures in Russian, which are held on other days.
We rely on Allah.
Allah will show a way out of this situation," he concluded.
But about 60% of us do not know the Tatar language.
These are Uzbeks, Tajiks and Azerbaijanis.
A lot goes to us foreign students: Africans, Arabs.
"That's why we have passed to the Russian language for four years," says the imam.
He believes that in the Tatar language the sermons will "reach a narrower circle and will not reach the whole audience."
But we will obey the decision of the plenum.
Just the result of the sermons will be different.
But time will show.
"For example, it will only be easier for me, because the Tatar language is my native," Gabdulla Galiullin concluded.
Former director of the Federal Penitentiary Service (FSIN) was sued
The Moscow Prosecutor's Office approved the indictment on the criminal case under the investigation of theft of budgetary funds allocated for the needs of the Federal Penitentiary Service of Russia.
Former head of the prison department Alexander Reimer and his deputy, who caused the FSIN damage in the amount of more than 2.7 billion rubles, will appear before the court.
The capital prosecutor's office sent a criminal case to the Zamoskvoretsky District Court against former director of the Federal Penitentiary Service of Russia Alexander Reimer, his former deputy Nikolai Krivolapov, as well as the director of FSUE "Center for Information and Technical Support and Communications of the Federal Penitary Service" (FSUP CITOS) Victor Definov.
Depending on the role and degree of participation in the commission of crimes, they are accused of the State Control Service of the Investigative Committee for Moscow under Part 3 of Article 285 of the Criminal Code (abuse of official powers, which caused grave consequences), Part 4 of Article 159 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (fraud committed with the use of his official position, as part of an organized group, on a particularly large scale).
In addition, Krivolapov is charged under Part 1 of Article 222 of the Criminal Code (illegal acquisition and storage of ammunition).
According to the TFR, in 2010-2012 these persons fraudulently stole from the state treasury budgetary funds allocated by the Federal Penitentiary Service to provide the department with electronic monitoring systems controlled by so-called electronic bracelets.
In order to steal budget money, the group's participants developed a scheme according to which the company controlled by him FSUE CITOS, with which the relevant state contracts were concluded, produced technical means of control and supervision, including "electronic bracelets," and implemented at prices inflated several times.
Despite the fact that FSUE CITOS did not have production equipment, buildings, facilities for the placement of production facilities, allowing to create a complete cycle of production of "electronic bracelets," five state contracts worth more than 3.3 billion rubles were concluded between him and the Federal Penitentiary Service of Russia.
As a result of this scheme, more than 2 billion rubles were stolen on the accounts of the Samara branch of the FSUE, of which 1.2 billion rubles were stolen.
According to the investigation, Mr. Raymer personally received more than 140 million rubles of cash in his office from one of the accomplice, the criminal case against which is allocated in separate proceedings.
Nikolai Krivolapov, who participated in the machinations, found unknown origin cartridges for the award pistol, which allowed him to make additional charges.
In this case, the amount of which amounted to 133 volumes, the Federal Penitentiary Service of Russia has filed a claim to compensate for material damage in the amount of 2.7 billion rubles.
Football player Hakana Shukura suspected of involvement in the putsch.
Turkish authorities issued a warrant to arrest a former footballer and then a member of the parliament Khakana Shukur and searched in two houses of his family.
The star of Turkish football of the 1990s - early 2000s striker Hakan Shukur is wanted by the authorities of the country in connection with an attempt of a coup d"état that last month.
Forward, who finished his sports career in 2008, is accused of belonging to the "armed terrorist group."
We are talking about the movement "Hizmet" - a society associated with the famous Turkish religious activist and oppositionist Fethullah Gulen.
It is his president Erdogan who considers the attempt of a military coup, which took place on July 15, as the organizer of the attempt.
Fethullah Gulen lives in the United States, the Turkish authorities demand his extradition.
According to local media, today a warrant was issued to arrest Khakana Shukur, the police have already searched in two houses, which belong to the family of the former footballer.
According to the investigators, in addition to Khakana Shukur, his father was also included in the organization of Fethullah Gulen.
However, neither the former footballer nor his relatives were there.
Now he and his family live in the United States.
As a footballer Hakan Shukur defended the colors of several Turkish clubs and played for the national team of the country.
He spent most of his career in Galatasaray.
The list of foreign clubs includes Italian "Torino," "Inter" and "Palermo," as well as English "Blackburn."
However, in none of them he spent more than one season.
Hakan Shukur is still the most productive striker of Turkey: in his asset 112 matches for the national team and 51 goals scored.
In 2013, Khakan Shukur resigned from his deputy due to the beginning of a corruption investigation around the Erdogan party and his closest circle.
