Bulgaria shows inflation for the first time in 8 months
Inflation in Bulgaria was 1 % monthly in July, as the national statistics show.
This is the highest indicator for the years (since June 2012) and the first above zero since October last year, when the positive 0.2 % was shown.
The average annual inflation measured by CPI in the last 12 months (August 2015 - July 2016) was -0,8 % compared to the previous 12 months (August 2014 - July 2015).
Consumer price index in July 2016 was 101.0% compared to June 2016, i.e. monthly inflation was 1.0 %.
The inflation rate since the beginning of the year (July 2016 compared to December 2015) was -0.2%, and the annual inflation in July 2016 compared to July 2015 was -0.2 %.
In July 2016, compared to the previous month, an increase was observed in the price of the following groups of consumer goods: food and non-alcoholic beverages (1.7 %); transportation (1.8 %); rest and culture (6,3 %); restaurants and hotels (1.2 %); other goods and services (0.3 %).
Prices decreased on clothes and shoes (2.2%); furniture, household appliances and regular maintenance (0.5 %); health (0.1 %).
Prices remained at the same level as in the previous month on alcoholic beverages and tobacco; housing conditions, water, electricity, gas and other fuels; communication systems; and education.
